Well, I went to this site and subscribed.  You cannot believe the self serving, psuedo-intellectual drivel that this site puts in it's archives!  The biggest site is around something called VVAVW.  Which stands for viet vets against the viet nam war.  The subscriptions stuff that was sent to my e-mail consisted of a bunch of liberal selfserving drivel about the whiners and cry baby Viet Nam vets who can't get over their experiences.<br>
It was an eye opener for me. Maybe I should have stuck around just to &quot;stir the pot&quot; as it were.  But it was scary that these are the educators and folks who are teaching the young people about the Sixties!<br>
Blew my socks off!  Oh, well if I ever get bored I know where I can go for some laughs and cheap entertainment.
